11:01.300 --> 11:03.834
When did you get
an engagement ring?

11:03.836 --> 11:05.002
My mother gave it to me,

11:05.004 --> 11:07.071
and I had been thinking
about giving it to you,

11:07.073 --> 11:08.539
but then we broke up.

11:08.541 --> 11:10.140
Well, thank goodness
for that.

11:10.142 --> 11:12.276
Sheldon, will you please tell
your grandmother

11:12.278 --> 11:13.677
to stay out of this?

11:13.679 --> 11:16.080
Oh, I don't think
I could do that.

11:16.082 --> 11:17.815
Sheldon, tell this girl

11:17.817 --> 11:20.751
that my ring will never be
on her finger.

11:20.753 --> 11:22.119
(sighs) Y...

11:22.121 --> 11:25.322
I'm gonna opt out
of that one, too.

11:25.324 --> 11:27.925
Who said I even want
to be engaged to him?

11:27.927 --> 11:29.793
And if I do, I-I don't need
your hand-me-downs!

11:29.795 --> 11:30.794
All right, all right!

11:30.796 --> 11:31.996
Look, l-let's all...

11:31.998 --> 11:33.364
let's remain calm

11:33.366 --> 11:34.665
and analyze this situation.

11:34.667 --> 11:36.867
Now, I realize that
you've only known each other

11:36.869 --> 11:38.035
for less than a day,

11:38.037 --> 11:40.838
but is it possible this
crankiness is because

11:40.840 --> 11:42.673
your cycles have synced?

11:42.675 --> 11:44.575
You leave the room

11:44.577 --> 11:46.443
and let the grown-ups talk.

11:46.445 --> 11:47.611
Now.

11:47.613 --> 11:50.547
Don't speak to him
like he's a child.

11:50.549 --> 11:54.018
Thank you. I'm gonna go next
door and play with Leonard.

11:57.490 --> 11:59.657
Okay, so you met this girl,
you exchanged numbers,

11:59.659 --> 12:01.091
and you're gonna
meet up with her.

12:01.093 --> 12:02.726
Just to help her
with her screenplay.

12:02.728 --> 12:04.628
Oh. Well,
I guess that's not so bad.

12:04.630 --> 12:05.663
You weren't there.

12:05.665 --> 12:06.897
He was really flirting.

12:06.899 --> 12:09.833
Hey, it's not my fault
if American women project

12:09.835 --> 12:11.235
their fantasies on foreigners

12:11.237 --> 12:15.039
with the kind of magical voice
that grants wishes.

12:15.041 --> 12:17.174
I'm sure it was harmless.

12:17.176 --> 12:18.542
People flirt. No big deal.

12:18.544 --> 12:20.511
Really? So it's
okay if I fl...

12:20.513 --> 12:22.680
Not you. I own your ass.

12:23.950 --> 12:26.884
The real question is,
where are you with Emily?

12:26.886 --> 12:28.752
Uh, it's hard to say.

12:28.754 --> 12:30.788
I think we're good,
but things like this

12:30.790 --> 12:33.257
make me wonder if Emily's
really the right person for me.

12:33.259 --> 12:35.326
I mean, did you guys ever have
doubts about each other?

12:35.328 --> 12:37.661
No. Never.
Absolutely.

12:37.663 --> 12:38.796
What?

12:38.798 --> 12:39.997
Howie, you forget

12:39.999 --> 12:41.332
how much of our early dates

12:41.334 --> 12:42.466
involved you doing magic

12:42.468 --> 12:44.168
and me doing this.

12:45.905 --> 12:47.471
Fine.

12:47.473 --> 12:49.606
I had reservations
about you, too.

12:49.608 --> 12:50.407
No, you didn't.

12:50.409 --> 12:52.009
No, I didn't.

12:52.011 --> 12:53.911
Well, it doesn't matter now,

12:53.913 --> 12:55.913
'cause I love
how things worked out.

12:55.915 --> 12:57.047
Me, too.

12:57.049 --> 12:58.949
And I think you're
even more beautiful

12:58.951 --> 13:01.151
than this rose.

13:06.425 --> 13:09.393
Wow. The last time
I saw my grandma,

13:09.395 --> 13:10.828
the most exciting thing
was watching the ash

13:10.830 --> 13:12.596
of her cigarette get longer
and wondering

13:12.598 --> 13:15.299
if it was gonna fall
in her pudding.

13:15.301 --> 13:17.034
Did it?

13:17.036 --> 13:18.035
Yeah, right in there.

13:18.037 --> 13:19.770
She ate it and everything.

13:19.772 --> 13:22.006
(knocking)
SHELDON: Leonard and Penny.

13:22.008 --> 13:23.741
Leonard and Penny.
Leonard and Penny.

13:23.743 --> 13:25.109
Come in!

13:25.111 --> 13:26.410
LEONARD:
Hey. What happened?

13:26.412 --> 13:27.611
Is Amy gone?

13:27.613 --> 13:29.346
No. They asked me to leave

13:29.348 --> 13:31.081
so they could speak privately.

13:31.083 --> 13:32.983
Uh-oh.
Yeah, I know. It was quite tense.

13:32.985 --> 13:35.652
So here's
the million dollar question:

13:35.654 --> 13:39.390
uh, who wants to pop over there
and get my trains?

13:42.194 --> 13:44.194
All right.
I've made up my mind.

13:44.196 --> 13:46.030
I'm gonna do the right thing,
call this girl,

13:46.032 --> 13:47.865
and let her know
that I'm in a relationship.

13:47.867 --> 13:48.999
Okay, so far we've heard,

13:49.001 --> 13:50.901
“made up my mind,
I'm dumping Emily.”

13:50.903 --> 13:52.636
“Made up my mind
to date both of them

13:52.638 --> 13:55.572
by pretending
to be twin brothers.”

13:56.442 --> 13:57.441
And “made up my mind,

13:57.443 --> 13:58.609
“I'll ask for a threesome

13:58.611 --> 14:01.311
and if they say no,
play it off as a joke.”

14:01.313 --> 14:02.679
I'm calling her.

14:02.681 --> 14:05.916
And the threesome didn't deserve
the belly laugh it got.

14:05.918 --> 14:07.551
You're right.

14:07.553 --> 14:11.021
(stifled laughter):
It could totally happen.

14:11.023 --> 14:12.089
CLAIRE:
Hello?

14:12.091 --> 14:13.657
Hi. Hi. Yeah, it's Raj.

14:13.659 --> 14:15.592
Rajesh.
We met at the comic book store.

14:15.594 --> 14:17.928
Hey, what's up? Figure out
what time you're free?

14:17.930 --> 14:19.296
Actually,
that's why I'm calling.

14:19.298 --> 14:20.664
I, um... I just...

14:20.666 --> 14:23.333
I need to let you know
that I have a girlfriend.

14:23.335 --> 14:25.269
Okay. Good for you.

14:26.072 --> 14:27.104
Well, no, no.

14:27.106 --> 14:28.272
I-I didn't want to mislead you

14:28.274 --> 14:29.573
after you asked me out.

14:29.575 --> 14:31.208
I didn't ask you out.

14:31.210 --> 14:33.077
I just need help
with my screenplay.

14:33.079 --> 14:35.612
Wait, are you saying
that we didn't have a vibe?

14:35.614 --> 14:37.781
Why do you care if we have
a vibe? You have a girlfriend.

14:37.783 --> 14:39.783
Come on! I just told you
I had a girlfriend.

14:39.785 --> 14:41.705
The least you can do is tell me
if we had a vibe.

14:43.322 --> 14:44.688
Sure, we had a vibe.

14:44.690 --> 14:46.490
I knew it.
Okay, we did have a vibe.

14:46.492 --> 14:47.791
This is exciting.

14:47.793 --> 14:49.960
What's my next move?

14:49.962 --> 14:51.328
You still have a girlfriend.

14:51.330 --> 14:53.497
Right. Good catch.

14:54.467 --> 14:56.133
Anyway, so I'm sorry
to waste your time.

14:56.135 --> 14:57.768
And, uh... and good luck
with your screenplay.

14:57.770 --> 14:59.103
Hang on.

14:59.105 --> 15:00.504
We're both adults.

15:00.506 --> 15:02.706
We can still get together
without it meaning anything.

15:02.708 --> 15:05.075
Not me. Ever since
you admitted we had a vibe,

15:05.077 --> 15:07.010
I've been planning our wedding.

15:08.414 --> 15:11.115
Look, it's just coffee.

15:11.117 --> 15:12.716
I'll ask you some questions
about science,

15:12.718 --> 15:15.552
and if you propose,
I promise to say no.

15:15.554 --> 15:18.789
Okay. That hurts a little,
but okay.

15:19.492 --> 15:21.024
Great. I'll text you.

15:21.026 --> 15:22.626
Bye.

15:22.628 --> 15:23.927
All right.

15:23.929 --> 15:26.864
So, uh, we're meeting
for coffee like two adults.

15:26.866 --> 15:28.765
Everybody's happy. Easy peasy.

15:28.767 --> 15:30.400
Are you gonna tell Emily?

15:30.402 --> 15:31.535
Yeah, of course.

15:31.537 --> 15:33.003
We have no secrets.

15:33.806 --> 15:35.539
When are you gonna tell Emily?

15:36.408 --> 15:38.609
He lied about the cream cheese!

15:38.611 --> 15:40.677
He ate the whole thing!
I saw him!

15:43.516 --> 15:46.016
Look, I know you think
I'm not right for Sheldon,

15:46.018 --> 15:48.018
but trust me,
I'm his best shot.

15:48.020 --> 15:50.521
You have no idea
how much I put up with!

15:50.523 --> 15:52.789
I know more than you think I do.

15:52.791 --> 15:54.925
Really? You know what it's like
to have date night ruined

15:54.927 --> 15:57.661
because Google changed
their font?

15:57.663 --> 15:59.663
Young lady,

15:59.665 --> 16:01.331
if you think I don't know

16:01.333 --> 16:02.566
what it's like to live

16:02.568 --> 16:04.668
with a stubborn,
egotistical man,

16:04.670 --> 16:06.003
then you're wrong.

16:06.005 --> 16:08.038
'Cause that was my husband.

16:08.040 --> 16:09.773
Really?

16:09.775 --> 16:11.008
(sighs)

16:11.010 --> 16:13.744
There were days I wanted to fill
his pockets with corn

16:13.746 --> 16:16.280
and toss him in the pigpen.

16:17.116 --> 16:19.349
Well, if you understand,

16:19.351 --> 16:22.019
then why are you giving me
such a hard time?

16:22.021 --> 16:24.121
Because when you broke up
with Sheldon,

16:24.123 --> 16:25.422
it hurt him deeply,

16:25.424 --> 16:27.858
and I don't want to see
that happen again.

16:27.860 --> 16:29.059
(door opens)

16:29.061 --> 16:31.028
Hi. Sorry.

16:31.030 --> 16:33.263
Sheldon would like
to say something to you.

16:33.265 --> 16:34.331
SHELDON:
No, I wouldn't.

16:34.333 --> 16:35.632
Just get in here.

16:37.036 --> 16:38.068
Hello.

16:38.070 --> 16:39.536
Go ahead.

16:39.538 --> 16:41.104
Meemaw, look,

16:41.106 --> 16:43.073
I'm sorry, but...

16:43.075 --> 16:44.374
I have to defend

16:44.376 --> 16:46.310
my girlfriend to you.

16:46.312 --> 16:48.612
Oh, Sheldon, thank you.

16:48.614 --> 16:51.215
Oh, great, now you're gonna
get emotional.

16:55.854 --> 16:59.456
I always looked up
to you and Pop-Pop.

16:59.458 --> 17:01.725
I-I know what
a challenging man he could be,

17:01.727 --> 17:05.061
but I saw you stand
by him and-and make him

17:05.064 --> 17:06.663
into a better person.

17:06.665 --> 17:07.698
I did.

17:07.700 --> 17:08.799
Yeah, well, that is exactly

17:08.800 --> 17:10.767
what I've been doing
the last five years

17:10.769 --> 17:13.002
with this little
work in progress.

17:15.773 --> 17:17.974
He never disappoints,
does he?

17:19.144 --> 17:22.179
I think what Sheldon means
to say is

17:22.181 --> 17:24.381
we've both grown together.

17:24.383 --> 17:25.449
Isn't that right?

17:25.451 --> 17:26.849
Well...

17:26.852 --> 17:27.317
Say yes.

17:27.319 --> 17:28.685
Yes.

17:28.687 --> 17:30.087
MEEMAW:
Fine.

17:30.089 --> 17:33.790
If you feel so strongly,
I won't stand in your way.

17:33.792 --> 17:35.025
Thank you.

17:35.027 --> 17:36.126
So if he wanted

17:36.128 --> 17:38.328
to give me
that engagement ring,

17:38.330 --> 17:40.364
we would have your blessing?

17:40.366 --> 17:42.366
I suppose.

17:47.673 --> 17:49.239
I just gave you
my virginity, woman.

17:49.241 --> 17:50.974
Cool your jets.

18:01.690 --> 18:04.591
Yeah, see, if you
just change the story

18:04.593 --> 18:06.727
to the destruction
of our <i> galaxy,</i>

18:06.729 --> 18:09.229
then a super massive
black hole could work.

18:09.231 --> 18:10.797
This is great.

18:10.799 --> 18:13.066
Thank you so much.

18:13.068 --> 18:14.968
I just got to figure out
a way for everyone

18:14.970 --> 18:17.638
to die that isn't too scary
for children.

18:19.275 --> 18:23.076
And that's how
Mommy and Daddy met.

18:24.546 --> 18:26.847
Hey, did you ever tell Emily
about us?

18:26.849 --> 18:28.315
I will!

